<subsection xml:id="subsec-operations-involving-fractions-in-real-life">
    <title>Operations involving fractions in real life</title>
   <p>
     Understanding how fractions work in real life is important because we use them in many everyday situations.
   </p> 
   <p>
        Fractions help us solve problems like : 
   </p>
   <p>
    <ol marker= "i)">
        <li>
            <p>
                Measuring quantities during cooking, construction,...
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Dividing resources while splitting bills, sharing items,...
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Calculating proportions like discounts, interest rates,...
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Managing time and tasks like scheduling lessons, fitness tracking,...
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Sharing and comparing things
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
   </p>
   <p>
     Whether it's figuring out how much of a recipe to make, dividing a pizza, or working out discounts while shopping, knowing how to add, subtract, multiply, and divide things.
     Fractions can make these tasks easier to handle.
   </p>
   <activity>
    <statement>
        <p>
            
        </p>
        <p>
         Aisha had the following conversation with her brother Malik and her sister Zara.
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Aisha:}</m>   Good morning.    
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>\textbf{Malik and Zara: }</m>Good morning Aisha.      
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Aisha:}</m> Here is the orange juice and mango juice you requested me to buy.    
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Zara:}</m>  Wow it will be enough for our friends   
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Malik:}</m>   How much did you spend on each of them?  
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Aisha: }</m> I spent <m>\frac{2}{5}</m> of the money I had to buy the orange juice and <m>\frac{1}{4}</m> of the money to buy the mango juice.
             I was left with sh <m> 350</m>.    
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Malik and Zara:}</m> Thank you for the juice sister.     
        </p>
        <p>
         <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Role-play the conversation.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Work out the fraction representing the amount of money Aisha spent to buy the two items.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Work out the fraction representing the remaining amount of money.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                   <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Calculate the total amount of money Aisha had initially.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            How much did Aisha spend on orange juice?

                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            How much did Aisha spend on mango juice?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                   </ol> 
                </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
   </activity>
   <example>
    <statement>
        <p>
          Cheptoo spends <m>\frac{1}{8}</m>  of her salary on food, <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> on rent, <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> of the remainder on school fees and saves the rest. 
          If she save sh <m> 4,200</m>, calculate:
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol marker="1">
                <li>
                    <p>
                       The fraction of the salary Cheptoo saved. 
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The amount of money she spent on food
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The amount of money she spent on rent.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The amount of money she spent on shool fees.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
       
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                     <p>
                      Let Cheptoo's salary be a whole number represented by <m>1</m> 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      Fraction of the remaining amount of money after spending on food and rent is:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Fraction of food <m>= \frac{1}{8}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Fraction of rent <m>= \frac{1}{2}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      <md>
                        <mrow> 1-(\frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{2}) \amp </mrow>
                        <mrow> \frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{2} =\amp \frac{1+4}{8}</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp \frac{5}{8}</mrow>
                        <mrow> 1- \frac{5}{8} =\amp \frac{1}{1} - \frac{5}{8}</mrow>
                        <mrow>\frac{8-5}{8} =\amp \frac{3}{8} </mrow>
                      </md>  
                    </p>
                   <p>
                      Fraction of school fees:
                                                <md>
                                                    <mrow> \frac{1}{2} \times \frac{3}{8}=\amp \frac{1 \times 3}{2 \times 8}</mrow>
                                                    <mrow> \amp </mrow>
                                                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{3}{16} </mrow>
                                      
                                                </md>  
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      Fraction of the money she spent on food,school fees and rent:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Food <m>= \frac{1}{8}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Rent <m>= \frac{1}{2}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        School fees <m>= \frac{3}{16}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow> \frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{2} + \frac{3}{16} =\amp \frac{2+8+3}{16} </mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp </mrow>
                            <mrow> =\amp \frac{13}{16}</mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                       Fraction of money she saved is:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow> \frac{1}{1} - \frac{13}{16} =\amp \frac{16 - 13}{16}</mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp </mrow>
                            <mrow> =\amp \frac{3}{16}</mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                </li>    
                <li>
                    <p>
                      The amount of money she spent on food, rent and school fees:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                     Since she saved sh <m> 4 200</m> and the fraction she saved is <m>\frac{3}{16}</m>, it means that <m>\frac{3}{16}</m> represents sh <m>4 200</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      The total salary represented by <m>1</m> is given by:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow>1 \times 4 200 \div \frac{3}{16} =\amp 1 \times 4 200 \times \frac{16}{3}</mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp </mrow>
                            <mrow> =\amp 4200 \times \frac{16}{3}</mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ol marker="i)">
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                   Amount spent on food = <m>\frac{1}{8}</m> of the total salary
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <md>
                                        <mrow> \frac{1}{8} \times 4200 \times \frac{16}{3} =\amp \frac{1}{\cancel{8}_1} \times \cancel{4200}^(1400) \times \frac{\cancel{16}^2}{\cancel{3}_1}</mrow>
                                        <mrow> \amp </mrow>
                                        <mrow>  =\amp \text{sh} 2800 </mrow>
                                    </md>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Amount spent on rent = <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> of the total salary
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <md>
                                        <mrow> \frac{1}{2} \times 4200 \times \frac{16}{3} =\amp \frac{1}{\cancel{2}_1} \times ^(1400)\cancel{4200} \times \frac{\cancel{16}^8}{\cancel{3}_1}  </mrow>
                                        <mrow> \amp </mrow>
                                        <mrow> =\amp \text{sh} 11 200</mrow>
                                    </md>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Amount spent on school fees = <m>\frac{3}{16}</m> of the total salary
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    But we already know that <m>\frac{3}{16}</m> represents sh <m>4 200</m>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Hence amount spent on school fees <m>= </m> sh <m> 4 200</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </solution>
   </example>
</subsection>
